With over 30,000 students in Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to provide services at the highest level to their students and parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare their students for high school and higher education, their chosen career and their place as global citizens.
As an educational sector that can conceive and implement a special school curriculum, we note that modern languages continue to be a popular and desired topic of choice within schools.
Nelson Mandela said, “If you speak to a man in a language he understands, your words will reach his mind.
If you speak to him in his own language, the words reach his heart.”
