Europe’s team captain Thomas Bjorn knows that the considerable advance may soon disappear
Thomas Bjorn, the captain of the Europeans, knows from the experience that the considerable advance held before the first day of the simple trials in the Ryder Cup can easily turn into an uncomfortable journey.
The Dane made his debut in the 1997 match at Valderrama, when the team led by Captain Seve Ballesteros led the Americans by five points, but barely managed to beat them by a minimal difference, from 141.2 to 131.2.
