A breast pump ad that compares women to cows divides public opinion online
A breast pump company has sparked the division of public opinion online with an ad comparing breastfeeding mothers to cow milking.
To mark the launch of a pump that aims to be “the world’s first silent and portable breast pump,” consumer technology company Elvie has launched an ironic music video-inspired ad to showcase the freedom the new pump offers nursing mothers.
Four real mothers dance in a barn full of hay for cows on a song that includes lyrics like, “Yes, I’m milking, but I don’t have a tail” and “if you haven’t noticed, they’re not bears, they’re my breasts.”
The chorus continues: “I pump, pump, breastfeed, pump, pump, extract milk from girls.”
However, the ad, posted on the company’s Facebook page, sparked controversy online.
With 77,000 views and hundreds of comments, the video was the target of mixed reactions from those who viewed it, many of them claiming to bring out the “horror” of the dairy industry.
“It was a very bad decision to use cows to promote this product.
“Like us, they must remain pregnant and be born to produce milk, except that their children are only stolen a few days after birth.”
Elvie breast pump discreetly fits into a breastfeeding bra (Elvie/mother)
Another person commented: “It’s understandable how traumatic it is for both mother and child.
Of course, why not use them to promote a breast pump for mothers who can keep their babies?”
Someone else added: “An extremely inappropriate advertisement.”
Others defended the ad, one person claiming it looked like a “hilarious” ad.
“I think it’s a brilliant idea.
I would have bought one if I were still breastfeeding.
Pumping really made me feel like a cow.
The claim is a bit inappropriate, but I took it as such.
But the product is brilliant,” one person wrote.
Another person commented: “It’s a funny ad targeting mothers who use the pump (often at work or in the toilet) and who feel like ‘empties.’
It’s not an advertisement that praises or judges the dairy industry.”
At the end of the video, the group of women reveal that they danced with discreet pumps inserted into their bras.
The concept behind the campaign is that many women who use the breast pump say they feel like cows.
But the Elvie pump is completely silent, has no wires or tubes and discreetly fits into a breastfeeding bra, giving women freedom of movement, the ability to hold their children in their arms, and even feeling alive while using the pump.
Ana Balarin, Partner, Consultant and Design Developer at Mother commented: “The Elvie Pump is such a revolutionary product that it deserves such a bold and challenging launch.
Comparing nursing mothers and dairy cows, we wanted to highlight what it means to use a breast pump and the challenges in this regard, presenting, in a fun and real way, the incredible feeling of freedom that the new pump will give.
